26:05.360 --> 26:06.160
Talk about that.

26:06.180 --> 26:08.703
I know you don't have a problem talking about that.

26:09.464 --> 26:10.004
I don't know.

26:10.024 --> 26:11.606
I had a bellyache.

26:13.908 --> 26:21.636
I was going to a doctor, and I asked him who it is.

26:22.797 --> 26:24.158
He said, I don't know.

26:25.100 --> 26:28.545
So baseball season was opening.

26:29.506 --> 26:32.470
The Brian Bomber was opening.

26:32.490 --> 26:35.414
So Francis and I were going to go to the ball camp.

26:36.355 --> 26:39.700
But about a quarter to six, I got a chill.

26:39.880 --> 26:40.661
Yes, sir.

26:40.681 --> 26:42.904
And I'd had pneumonia about four times.

26:43.605 --> 26:47.210
So I thought, well, if you get pneumonia, so I go on emergency.

26:48.151 --> 26:49.713
That's when they found the cancer.

26:49.733 --> 26:50.033
Yes, sir.

26:50.815 --> 26:51.175
Yes, sir.

26:51.779 --> 27:04.818
I mean, they put me in the hospital, and they put me on the... He did a CAT scan, and they said it's pancreatic and liver cancer, which is terminal.

27:04.839 --> 27:07.082
Yes, sir.

27:07.102 --> 27:07.803
But you're not afraid.

27:10.607 --> 27:11.909
You're not afraid.

27:11.929 --> 27:13.051
That's what you told me.

27:13.952 --> 27:15.675
You're... I gotta go.

27:15.695 --> 27:16.997
I gotta go sometime.

27:17.137 --> 27:18.459
Yes, sir.

27:18.479 --> 27:19.260
Yes, sir.

27:19.280 --> 27:21.263
And, like I say, I...

27:23.032 --> 27:26.515
When I was a kid, I never figured I'd get 85.

27:26.535 --> 27:27.436
85.

27:29.598 --> 27:33.722
So I just only had my share.

27:34.122 --> 27:34.482
Yes, sir.

27:35.483 --> 27:37.625
A wonderful and a very proud life.

27:38.006 --> 27:39.887
And we wish you the best.

27:39.968 --> 27:41.969
And we thank you very, very much for your service.

27:41.989 --> 27:46.453
